We can use a switch statement when we have multiple if-else nested. It makes much easier to read the code.
The syntax for a switch statement is the following:

switch(variable){
	case 1: statement; break;
	case 2: statement; break;
	case n: statement; break;
	default: statement; break;
}

Exercise. 
1. Make a menu using a switch statement.
	Option 1. Make a conversion from USD to MXN
	Option 2. Make a conversion from MXN to USD
	Option 3. Show menu again.
	Option 4. Exit